<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <!--
    Better Traders Guild - Bounded Defender Duty

    BTG_DefendStructure: Combat-engaged defensive posture that never assaults.
    Pawns with this duty, in priority order:
    1. Withdraw-and-tend when critically wounded, via JobGiver_BTGWithdrawAndTend.
       This sits ABOVE combat: a defender too badly hurt to fight without risking
       immediate death (bleeding heavily OR low overall health) breaks off, ducks
       out of enemy line of sight inside the structure, tends its worst wounds,
       then returns to the fight. The withdraw cell is constrained to the
       structure footprint, so it never flees into vacuum. No-op for mechs
       (Humanlike-gated). Distinct from node 3 below, which only tends when no
       target remains; this one fires even with hostiles in line of sight.
    2. Acquire and engage hostile targets, but only inside the settlement
       structure (target acquisition filtered by JobGiver_BTGDefendStructure).
       Combat outranks ordinary needs, so a defender never breaks off to eat (or
       to tend non-critical wounds) while a valid in-structure target remains.
    3. Seek treatment in the medbay when wounded but unable to self-tend, via
       JobGiver_BTGSeekTreatmentInMedbay. A defender that has tendable wounds but
       lacks Manipulation (e.g. both arms shot off) is invisible to the vanilla
       self-tend node below - which also needs Manipulation - so without this it would
       just stand and bleed. It walks to a free medical bed inside a medbay room and
       lies down for the paramedic mech to tend. Bounded to medbay beds specifically
       (not just the structure), because medical beds exist only there and the
       medbay-confined medic can reach nowhere else; no-op when none is free. Downed
       pawns are excluded - those are the medic's rescue job. Gates on Manipulation
       alone, the exact complement of self-tend (whose Doctor-disabled guard is
       colonist-only, skipped for these faction pawns), so the two partition the
       wounded with no overlap. No-op for mechs (Humanlike-gated).
    4. Self-tend wounds when not in combat. JobGiver_SelfTend tends in place (no
       pathing), so it needs no containment. No-op for mechs (Humanlike-gated).
    5. Eat when hungry, via JobGiver_BTGForageInStructure: carried rations first,
       then the best food item that lies inside the structure footprint (never a
       corpse - eating the dead is beneath the guild). Once
       urgently hungry with no item food left, two in-structure "last resort"
       sources, in order: crack open survival-meal pallets, then dispense from
       nutrient-paste dispensers / VNPE taps. Raw crops from the hydroponics are
       deliberately NOT foraged - wealthy guild traders escalate hunger with a
       packaged-meal resupply drop (the comms-console path), not unprepared
       produce. It never targets food outside the structure, so a player cannot
       bait a hungry defender out by dropping food past the walls. (Replaces
       vanilla JobGiver_GetFood, whose unbounded map search has no location
       filter.)
    6. Call a resupply when starving, via JobGiver_BTGCallResupply: only once every
       in-structure food source above is exhausted (gated to Starving, one rung past
       the forager's UrgentlyHungry), a defender walks to a powered in-structure comms
       console and calls in a survival-meal cargo-pod drop. The drop lands in an
       in-structure room (ResupplyDropUtility's priority list), so this stays in-bounds.
       A per-map cooldown keeps the garrison from all calling at once; with several
       consoles it is enforced at call completion, so only the first defender to finish
       triggers a drop and starts the cooldown - the rest abort. No-op for mechs.
    7. Break out to eat when starving and walled in, via JobGiver_BTGHackDoorForFood:
       a pawn that spawned trapped behind a locked AncientBlastDoor can reach none of
       the food above (nor a comms console), so as a last resort it hacks the nearest
       reachable, still-locked blast door open, then re-evaluates - the forage/resupply
       nodes can finally path to food. Below resupply and gated to Starving, so it only
       fires when a pawn truly is sealed off. Stays in-bounds: BTG's perimeter is sealed
       by VacBarriers (not blast doors), so every hackable door is interior. All hack
       eligibility is delegated to vanilla CompHackable.CanHackNow. No-op for mechs.
    8. Rest when tired, via JobGiver_BTGRestInStructure: only reached once nothing
       above wants the pawn (no combat target, wounds, or hunger), so the ordering
       itself is the "no immediate threat" gate. Reuses vanilla bed/ground-spot
       selection but rejects any spot outside the structure footprint, so a defender
       never paths out to sleep. Waking is fully native: while asleep the LayDown
       toil re-runs this tree every 211 ticks (combat is above this node, so a
       hostile re-entering the perimeter pulls the defender back into the fight
       within ~3.5s), and taking damage wakes it the same tick. No-op for mechs.
    9. Fall back to wandering near the focus point (radius 12) when idle.

    Containment summary - defenders never leave the structure because:
      * combat targets are filtered to the union of room rects, and
        JobGiver_AIDefendPoint (chaseTarget=false) holds firing positions within
        the duty radius of baseCenter rather than pursuing, and
      * foraging is restricted to food inside the same rect union, and
      * resupply drops land in an in-structure room and the calling defender only
        paths to an in-structure comms console, and
      * break-out hacking only targets interior blast doors (the perimeter is sealed
        by VacBarriers), so unlocking one never opens a path to vacuum, and
      * rest beds / sleep spots are constrained to the same rect union, and
      * the seek-treatment node only targets a medical bed inside a medbay room, and
      * self-tend and idle wander are in-place / focus-local.

    Used by: LordJob_BTGDefendStructure, assigned to the mapgen settlement
    defender group (human guards + gestator-spawned mechs). The forager is inert
    for mechs (no food need) but live for human guards.

    Design intent: model a "reverse siege" where defenders hold an entrenched,
    terrain-advantaged position and never path out of the structure to chase
    intruders or forage.
  -->

  <DutyDef>
    <defName>BTG_DefendStructure</defName>
    <thinkNode Class="ThinkNode_Priority">
      <subNodes>
        <!-- 1. Critically wounded: withdraw out of LoS (inside the structure) and
             tend before resuming the fight. Preempts combat by design. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGWithdrawAndTend" />
        <!-- 2. Combat: engage in-structure targets before any ordinary need. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGDefendStructure" />
        <!-- 3. Wounded but can't self-tend (no Manipulation - e.g. both arms shot off):
             walk to a free medical bed inside the medbay and lie down for the paramedic
             mech to tend. Complements the self-tend node below (which also needs
             Manipulation), so the two never overlap; downed pawns are excluded (the medic
             rescues those). No-op for mechs and when no in-medbay bed is free. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGSeekTreatmentInMedbay" />
        <!-- 4. Self-tend when not in combat (in place; no containment needed). -->
        <li Class="JobGiver_SelfTend" />
        <!-- 5. Eat, restricted to food inside the structure footprint. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGForageInStructure">
          <minCategory>Hungry</minCategory>
        </li>
        <!-- 6. Starving with no in-structure food left: use an in-structure comms console
             to call in a survival-meal cargo-pod resupply. Below the forager, so real food
             is always tried first; gated one rung past it (Starving vs UrgentlyHungry). The
             pod lands inside the structure, so this stays in-bounds like everything else. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGCallResupply">
          <minCategory>Starving</minCategory>
        </li>
        <!-- 7. Starving and sealed off: a pawn that spawned trapped behind a locked
             AncientBlastDoor can reach no food or comms console above, so it hacks the
             nearest reachable blast door open as a last resort, then re-evaluates. Below
             resupply, gated to Starving. Only interior doors exist to hack (perimeter is
             VacBarriers), so this stays in-bounds. Eligibility = vanilla CompHackable.
             CanHackNow. No-op for mechs. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGHackDoorForFood">
          <minCategory>Starving</minCategory>
        </li>
        <!-- 8. Rest when tired, but only once nothing above wants the pawn (no combat
             target, wounds, or hunger). Reuses vanilla bed/spot selection, constrained
             to the structure footprint. Defenders wake natively: the LayDown toil
             re-checks this tree every 211 ticks (combat sits above), and damage wakes
             them the same tick. No-op for mechs (no rest need). -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGRestInStructure">
          <minRestCategory>Tired</minRestCategory>
        </li>
        <!-- 9. Idle: wander near the focus point. -->
        <li Class="JobGiver_WanderNearDutyLocation">
          <wanderRadius>12</wanderRadius>
        </li>
      </subNodes>
    </thinkNode>
  </DutyDef>

</Defs>
